NSIA Insurance has stated that it is determined to drive insurance acceptance across the twelve African countries where it exists. The underwriter began the year 2022 with the initiative called ‘Project Act Together’ to help the insurance industry to develop and evolve a consistent mindset across the insurer business operations. The organisation said subsidiaries within NSIA Group would combine their distinct talents to propel the insurance business and foster relationships between employees and management while improving work conditions. WAGPA Gets New Boss Okomu Oil Plc Generates N37bn In 2021 Ebelechukwu Nwachukwu, the Managing Director/ Chief Executive Officer of the firm, said: “’Project Act Together is a great initiative that will improve working relationships and promote cohesion among NSIA subsidiaries in Africa. NSIA Nigeria will continue to instil the 12 common goals and connect its culture with the Group.” According to her, the project began with a message from the Group President, Jean Kacou Diagou, on January 4, 2022. NSIA subsidiaries across Africa tuned in to listen to the message and learn about the 2021 accomplishments as well as 2022 goals.